  (text "J2 PINOUT (1x6 2.54mm, mates with UNO Q JSPI):\n  Pin 1: SPI_MOSI (from STM32U585)\n  Pin 2: SPI_MISO (to STM32U585)\n  Pin 3: SPI_SCK  (from STM32U585)\n  Pin 4: CS_S3_MCU (GPIO10, active LOW)\n  Pin 5: GND\n  Pin 6: +3V3 (reference only — do not draw current from UNO Q header)\n\nJ3 PINOUT (1x2 2.54mm, debug header):\n  Pin 1: UART_TX (GPIO47) — S3 debug output\n  Pin 2: GND\n  Use a USB-UART adapter at 115200 baud to read S3 debug output.\n  On Super Carrier, GPIO47 is S3→C6 UART TX — this header is DNP on carrier.\n\nCS_S3_MPU NOTE:\n  CS_S3_MPU (GPIO0) is NOT present on the shield.\n  The QRB2210 MPU is not accessible via UNO Q top headers.\n  CS_S3_MPU is only used on the Super Carrier via JMISC (B1).\n  GPIO0 has a 10kΩ pullup on both shield and carrier PCBs\n  to ensure safe boot even when CS_S3_MPU is unused."
    (at 20 100 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
)
